com.gwtplatform.mvp.client.proxy

Interface NonLeafTabContentProxy<P extends Presenter<?,?>>

  • Type Parameters:
    P - The type of the Presenter associated with this proxy.
    All Superinterfaces:
    HasHandlers, Proxy<P>, ProxyRaw, TabContentProxy<P>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    NonLeafTabContentProxyImpl

    public interface NonLeafTabContentProxy<P extends Presenter<?,?>>
extends TabContentProxy<P>
    The interface for the Proxy of a Presenter that does not have a name token and that can be displayed within a TabContainerPresenter's main area. Useful, among other things, for tabs within tabs. If the presenter is associated to a name token use TabContentProxyPlace instead. Example of use: 
     @ProxyCodeSplit
 @TabInfo(container = MainPagePresenter.class, priority = 0,
          label = "Home", nameToken = "homepage")
 public interface MyProxy extends NonLeafTabContentProxy<ThisPresenter> { }
    In this case, the nameToken parameter indicates the presenter to reveal when this tab is selected.
    Author:
    Philippe Beaudoin
    See Also:
    TabInfo

      • changeTab

        void changeTab(TabData tabData,
             String targetHistoryToken)
        Changes the data and target history token associated with this tab. This will automatically cause the displayed tab to change, provided the TabContainerPresenter containing this tab defines a ChangeTab field and passes it to the parent constructor.
